    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="423"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                        Commanding General, United States Forces, China Theater</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wedemeyer</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="58a" xml:id="d423fn58a">Sent also to Fleet Admiral
                        Nimitz.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-18">18 September
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Warx 66085. It is U. S. policy to assist the Chinese Government in the
                    establishment of essential Chinese troops in liberated areas, particularly
                    Manchuria, as rapidly as practicable.</p>
                <p>Movement of Chinese Forces will be executed, in so far as practicable, in general
                    conformity with the schedule indicated in Wedemeyer’s CFBX 8412 dated 17
                    September 1945,<note n="59" xml:id="d423fn59">Not found in Department
                        files.</note> utilizing for this purpose shipping now under your control. To
                    effect this movement, maximum use will be made of shipping unsuitable for
                    trans-Pacific use.</p>
                <p>Request you report to the Joint Chiefs of Staff, with information copy to
                    CinCAFPac, the action you take to move Chinese Forces in compliance with this
                    directive.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
